        <name>10.3.2.4 Finding the exponential form</name>
        <questiontext>&lt;p class="HELM_exercise"&gt;Exercise&lt;/p&gt;
Express the complex number \(z = \displaystyle{@zed@}\)&amp;nbsp; in exponential form. The argument of \(z\) should be given precisely in terms of \(\pi\), i.e. do not give your answer in decimal form:&lt;p&gt;\(z=\quad\)[[input:ans1]][[validation:ans1]]&amp;nbsp;[[feedback:prt1]]&lt;/p&gt;</questiontext>
        <questiontextformat>1</questiontextformat>
        <generalfeedback>&lt;p&gt;We want to express \(z\) in the form \(re^{i\theta}\).&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;We calculate \(r = \sqrt{({@re@})^2 + ({@im@})^2} = {@arr@}\) and \(\theta = \tan^{-1}\left({@im@}/{@re@}\right) = {@th@}\).&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Therefore: \[z = {@arr@}e^{{@th@}i}.\]&lt;/p&gt;</generalfeedback>
